          "id": 3,
          "text": "Bulla"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: B) Pustule</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>A <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0fd6c2af6d169277719639d2c79d03\">pustule</span> is a small, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"89aa50eac91692777184c8f668d2cf\">circumscribed</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a1f256489a16927771870ddd296574\">elevation</span> of the skin containing pus. They typically appear as small, white or yellowish bumps on the skin's surface. Pustules may have a visible central point where the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e4626b4cea16927771968e59732fef\">pus</span> is located.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Saurabh R. Patil,\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY-SA 3.0\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:A_pustule.jpg\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"2749\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/TdeSTcbT6Yb0mYk2Pv0I1733922366.png\" width=\"3986\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Wheal (Option A):</strong> Wheal is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a6cf2c3dc51692777200ef7fb22f69\">transient</span> type of skin <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d5e7bb15851692777191b39417c26a\">lesion</span> characterized by edematous, swollen and elevated <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"521e76df7d1692777186faf836b3f8\">dermis</span> and hypodermis.</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Allergyresearch,\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY-SA 4.0\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Hives_Urticaria.jpg\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"2504\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/LOkhcYC79DtxdpFPe39D1733922385.png\" width=\"3986\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Nodules (Option C):</strong> Nodules are solid, palpable, elevated masses that extend into the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"521e76df7d1692777186faf836b3f8\">dermis</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d446e62c6c1692777199896fc1d4b9\">subcutaneous</span> tissue. They are larger and deeper than papules, which are similar in appearance but smaller. They are >1 cm in size and range in depth from 1 to 10 mm.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Kaminska-Winciorek, Grazyna & Wydmański, Jerzy & Januszewski, Krzysztof & Silny, Wojciech.\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY-NC-ND 3.0\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/An-example-of-a-macroscopic-picture-of-a-meta-static-nodule-originating-from_fig5_281852640\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"3972\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/YLb7LASO37ah3E13Pe1J1733922400.png\" width=\"3954\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Bullae (Option D):</strong> Bullae are blisters more than 1 cm on the skin that are filled with clear fluid </p>",
