      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: D) Purpura</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Purpura is a primary skin lesion. It is a condition with red, discoloured spots on the skin that do not blanch on pressure. The spots are caused by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> underneath the skin.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Leonardo M. Lustosa, \" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY-SA 4.0\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Kirmisson%27s_and_pucker_sign.jpg\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"870\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/NJCAdTwAyh50DY298JlW1733922610.png\" width=\"521\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Purpura </strong>measure between 4 and 10 mm in diameter.</li>\n\t<li>When <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0acd34c758169277719644923511e5\">purpura</span> spots are less than 4 mm in diameter, they are called <strong>Petechiae.</strong></li>\n\t<li>Purpura spots larger than 1 cm are called <strong>Ecchymoses</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>All the below lesions are secondary skin lesions.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Atrophy (Option A): </strong>Atrophy refers to the loss of tissue from either or all the layers of skin (Epidermis, Dermis, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d446e62c6c1692777199896fc1d4b9\">Subcutaneous</span> tissue). If the process is superficial, there may be fine wrinkling and translucency.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Induration (Option B): </strong>Induration refers to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"532334711316927771865e5309b763\">dermal</span> thickening that clinically appears firmer than normal on palpation.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Crust (Option C): </strong>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"62b976e2941692777185c4b2eb180b\">crust</span> consists of dried-up <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9dd87431ba1692777186ecfb21d258\">discharge</span> from the lesions.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Köse, Murat & Buraniqi, Ersida & Akpınar, Timur & Kayacan, Seyit & Tükek, Tufan.\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Crusted-raised-skin-lesion-with-regular-borders_fig1_272516512\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"3330\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/TwNVYcy8U1OUaKGD75F31733922630.png\" width=\"3986\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>",
