    {
      "text": "Identify the skin lesion and the disease associated with the image below.",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Fissures - Seborrheic dermatitis"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Atrophy - Pityriasis rosea"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Target lesions - Pityriasis Versicolor"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Scales - Seborrheic dermatitis"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: D) Scales - <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5d5241c3cf1692777198a1ba71f8d4\">Seborrheic</span> dermatitis</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Scales are visible <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"812a17cdc91692777187972f882a13\">exfoliation</span> of the skin containing flakes of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5435715e1b1692777199602bdc830a\">stratum</span> corneum.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"3088\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/zNIiMQ0XTuy6GHEscuM31747692283.png\" width=\"4167\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Seborrheic dermatitis:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Seborrheic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fedc53b3161692777186553c8f8d7d\">dermatitis</span> is characterized by <strong>yellow, greasy scales</strong> covering the <strong>scalp</strong>, extending to the <strong>hairline</strong> and <strong>behind the ears.</strong></li>\n\t<li>Seborrheic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fedc53b3161692777186553c8f8d7d\">dermatitis</span> is a common <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9d21dd5d3116927771907405b181bc\">inflammatory</span> skin condition primarily affecting areas rich in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"359edf0778169277719886070af9db\">sebaceous</span> glands, such as the scalp, face, and trunk.</li>\n\t<li>It is characterized by erythematous plaques with adherent, greasy scales, often associated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8f179d376f16927771905338bc9387\">itching</span> and mild redness.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Fissures (Option A)</strong> are <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d02067c4b51692777191b8eec8b062\">linear</span> breaks or cracks in the skin that are not typically associated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5d5241c3cf1692777198a1ba71f8d4\">seborrheic</span> dermatitis.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"4167\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/i6zWEqfzSUYK87zSVAfq1747692302.png\" width=\"2928\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Atrophy (Option B)</strong> describes the thinning of the skin, resulting in a decrease in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"facd67f6341692777200653d383689\">thickness</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e4c62a77731692777187b9c7ded25d\">epidermis</span> and dermis. Pityriasis rosea is not typically associated with atrophy.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"4167\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/ksFlFHTuIOp9Og5lmHAl1747692322.png\" width=\"4167\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Target lesions (Option C) </strong>are less than 3 cm in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"afb15e4a331692777186e495b370a1\">diameter</span> and have three or more zones, usually a central area of dusky <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f0f3e105661692777187df507b1f26\">erythema</span> or purpura, a middle paler zone of oedema, and an outer ring of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f0f3e105661692777187df507b1f26\">erythema</span> with a well‐defined edge.</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"CDC/ James Gathany\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"open access\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Erythema_migrans_-_erythematous_rash_in_Lyme_disease_-_PHIL_9875.jpg?uselang=en#Licensing\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"982\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/ehx44I8YfUQ4wonfnDEO1733923045.png\" width=\"841\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<p>Pityriasis <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d8978d146e169277720159cb0f2631\">versicolor</span> presents with hypo- or hyperpigmented macules with fine scaling, but it is not typically associated with target lesions.</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Sarahrosenau \" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY SA 2.0\" data-source=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tinea_versicolor\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"1851\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/LPA3tSEpZyalwLJFOqMN1733923063.png\" width=\"3870\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>",
