    {
      "text": "A 45-year-old male presents with complaints of severe itching and thickened skin on his lower legs. Upon examination, well-demarcated areas of thickened, leathery skin with exaggerated skin markings are seen. He mentions that he has a history of atopic dermatitis and has been using topical corticosteroids intermittently for the past few years to manage flare-ups. Which of the following lesions is present in this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Erosion"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Ulcer"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Poikiloderma"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Lichenification"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: D) Lichenification</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation: </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Lichenification is characterised by the thickening of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e4c62a77731692777187b9c7ded25d\">Epidermis</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"521e76df7d1692777186faf836b3f8\">dermis</span> due to prolonged scratching.</li>\n\t<li>It is a secondary skin <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d5e7bb15851692777191b39417c26a\">lesion</span> associated with thick skin, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"30261213bf16927771898b5d2f245d\">hyperpigmentation</span> and exaggerated skin markings.</li>\n\t<li>It is associated with the following characteristic features in HPE\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Acanthosis (thickening of the epidermis)</li>\n\t\t<li>Hyperkeratosis (thickening of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5435715e1b1692777199602bdc830a\">stratum</span> corneum)</li>\n\t\t<li>Elongation of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6ab8d08a6516927771970811a428d8\">rete</span> ridges</li>\n\t\t<li>Chronic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9d21dd5d3116927771907405b181bc\">inflammatory</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8fd5e2898d16927771900855b98180\">infiltrate</span> in the dermis.</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"kilbad,\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY 3.0\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Lichen_simplex_chronicus_2.jpg\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"2548\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/T9ABX0zM6vK2t8XBG7dD1733923169.png\" width=\"3814\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<ul>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Erosion (Option A)</strong> is a loss of the epidermis, which heals without scarring.</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Madhero88,\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY-SA 3.0\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Ulcers,_fissures,_and_erosions.svg\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"2662\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/4CFj7ZjQwahYdm1VEB0v1733923183.png\" width=\"3820\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Ulcer (Option B)</strong> is a loss of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"521e76df7d1692777186faf836b3f8\">dermis</span> and epidermis, often with loss of the underlying tissues.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Poikiloderma (Option A)</strong> is an association of</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Cutaneous <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b5f46d7e431692777195efd6b43e9f\">pigmentation</span> (Hypo or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8b388efd711692777189df2d1fc1e4\">Hyper</span> pigmentation)</li>\n\t<li>Atrophy</li>\n\t<li>Telangiectasia (Visible <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"29a08d8f9216927771869ed797367e\">dilatation</span> of small blood vessels, particularly the capillaries, in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"532334711316927771865e5309b763\">dermal</span> layer of the skin).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Singh, Gautam & Arora, Sandeep & Das, Pankaj & Singh, Vikram & Gupta, Akanksha & Sharma, Vishal.\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY-SA NC 4,0\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/a-c-Clinical-photographs-showing-poikiloderma-involving-entire-body-d-Clinical_fig1_363365981\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"2573\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/8yRKaHwOzsDX2Pr6QQ891733923260.png\" width=\"3890\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>",
